summary:
Honestly, shout out to the Good Omens miniseries for bringing back my only good memories of middle school.
I’m just sitting here...
body:
Honestly, shout out to the Good Omens miniseries for bringing back my only good memories of middle school.

I’m just sitting here reblogging GO content like its 2009 and I’ve just come home from hanging out in the strip mall Borders with my friends after a half day at school. Just the good ol’ days of huddling in the YA/Manga section reading GO while my friends make suggestions to moms trying to buy book for their teens and Borders employees calling us the reading rainbow. A 100% wholesome middle school experience! Thanks Neil!

summary: Aziraphale is in love with Crowley. We know that. Every gesture he makes, the little glances, the smiles and eyes that linger...
body: Aziraphale is in love with Crowley. We know that. Every gesture he makes, the little glances, the smiles and eyes that linger just a little too long. But why is no one talking about Crowley? That demon literally asked Aziraphale to move in, to run with him, to go off together MULTIPLE times. He might not show the subtleties that Aziraphale does, but that doesn’t matter, does it? Crowley’s type of love isn’t gentle and soft, it’s grabbing you by the hand and screaming in your face I LOVE YOU without saying a single damn word because that type of love it’s just obvious. Crowley fell deep and hard for Aziraphale in the very moment he had a conversation with him and he’s not sure what to do about it. So, yeah, Aziraphale loves Crowley. But Crowley loves Aziraphale just as much, and I think we should talk about that too.

summary: As some one who read the book and loved the book, I am so happy to see Good Omens gaining popularity. My dash has been flooded...
body: As some one who read the book and loved the book, I am so happy to see Good Omens gaining popularity. My dash has been flooded with good omens stuff ever since the mini series aired and whether you’re an old fan or a new fan, I love that literally fucking everyone is in love with one of my favorite stories in the world. For those of you who have only read the book: watch the show! And for those of you who have only watched the show: read the book! They’re both amazing in their own way and if you enjoyed one I know you’ll enjoy the other.
